==Introduction==
Trainz '''scenery assets''' are the heart and soul of Trainz' ability to depict a three-dimensional alternate reality in creating and allowing us to operate or build virtual worlds. They can be amazingly simple, or extremely complex dynamic animated objects which include {{n3V|TrainzScript Language Reference|Trainz scripting features}}. After the TS2009 data model solidified, a former similar grouping of assets, "Trackside" objects (with attachments to track splines, usually containing an offset and direction from the track they are attached onto) were gradually altered to a new standard which uses a {{N3V|Class Trackside|Trackside Class}}, so that both used the same base {{TRC|scenery-container}}

