{{Use British English|date=August 2013}} {{Use dmy dates|date=February 2014}} {{Infobox officeholder |name = Ruby Yadav |image = File:Ruby yadav 31.jpg |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1980|5|14|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Meerut]], [[India]] |death_date = |death_place = |party = [[Independent (politician)|Independent]] |religion = [[Hinduism]] |website = [http://www.rubyyadav.com Official Website] }}
'''Ruby Yadav''' (born May 14, 1980) is winner of Mrs . India Queen Runner up in 2013 and secure 4th place in [[Loksabha]] election 2014 with 56,749 votes . The beauty queen came fourth in the general elections, leaving behind candidates from Trinamul Congress, Communist Party of India and Bahujan Samaj Party.Ruby was associated with Anna Hazare in his anti-corruption movement.Independent candidate from South Delhi and beauty queen Ruby Yadav made a spectacular debut by garnering the second highest vote share of all Independents across the seven constituencies in the national Capital.
She was born in [[Muzzafarnagar]], Uttar Pradesh, India. Yadav's initial schooling was at S.D. Public School, Muzzafarnagar. She then received her master's degree in organic chemistry from [[Chaudhary Charan Singh University]] (then Meerut University). In 2004, she married Vinay Yadav, a businessman from [[Rajokri]], [[New Delhi]]. She is well known social worker in Delhi .
