=Comparison of INRIX and NPMRDS Data Sets=
A comparison of speed data between INRIX and NPMRDS for January 2012 on a 4-lane inter-regional and 6-lane urban freeway.
{| class="wikitable" |- ! Urban 6-lane Freeway !! INRIX !! NPMRDS |- | Mean Speed (mph)|| align="center" | 61.05 || align="center" | 56.90 |- | Standard Deviation (mph) || align="center" | 4.61 || align="center" | 6.24 |- | Median Speed (mph)|| align="center" | 61.72 || align="center" | 58.05 |}
{| class="wikitable" |- ! IR 4-lane Freeway !! INRIX !! NPMRDS |- | Mean Speed (mph)|| align="center" | 65.32 || align="center" | 63.42 |- | Standard Deviation (mph) || align="center" | 3.69 || align="center" | 4.83 |- | Median Speed (mph)|| align="center" | 65.49 || align="center" | 64.00 |}
Particularly on the urban freeway, the NPMRDS data reports lower speeds than INRIX with higher variability. The matched pair graphs below reveal a similar trend represented by the linear fit with the intercept set to zero.
