== Categories == <big> * {{stage short|50%}} '''[[/Game logic/]]''' ::: The general set up that most games fit around * {{stage short|25%}} '''[[/Mathematics/]]''' ::: Basic Math, Vectors, Matrices, Trigonometry, Calculus, Quaternions * {{stage short|25%}} '''[[/Geometry/]]''' ::: The drawing of the objects in the scene, e.g. the player, enemies, terrain, boxes * {{stage short|0%}} '''[[/Transformations/]]''' ::: Translation (Movement), Scale, Rotation * {{stage short|0%}} '''[[/Camera/]]''' ::: The view-port that the game is viewed from. Perspective & Orthographic projects. * {{stage short|25%}} '''[[/Lighting/]]''' ::: The Lighting that's cast onto the scene. Ambient, Diffuse, Specular lighting, Normal vectors and Lightmaps. * {{stage short|25%}} '''[[/Graphical User Interfaces (GUI) and Heads-up-displays (HUD)/]]''' ::: The menus that the user navigates and the displays that appear on top of the game to display statistics like health. * {{stage short|25%}} '''[[/Collision detection/]]''' ::: How all of the entities in the game collide with each other and the terrain. * {{stage short|25%}} '''[[/Physical motion/]]''' ::: The physics/mechanics behind the motion, forces and gravity. * {{stage short|0%}} '''[[/Textures/]]''' ::: How textures are loaded, stored and placed onto geometry. * {{stage short|0%}} '''[[/Shaders and Graphic pipelines/]]''' ::: How the geometry, camera and lighting in a scene gets processed from the scene to the screen. * {{stage short|0%}} '''[[/Artificial Intelligence/]]''' ::: Programming of intelligence into a computer/bot/enemy. * {{stage short|0%}} '''[[/Animations/]]''' ::: In game animations * {{stage short|0%}} '''[[/User inputs/]]''' ::: How you handle user inputs and how they affect things in the game * {{stage short|25%}} '''[[/Viewing angles/]]''' ::: The topic of different types of game genres and how to create for that genre * {{stage short|25%}} '''[[/Miscellaneous theory/]]''' ::: Everything else to do with theory </big>
